-Are we?

19:33.120 --> 19:37.568
You know how long it's been since
I could actually play with someone?

19:37.960 --> 19:40.110
All I've had is solitaire.

19:42.750 --> 19:44.706
Cards?
-Two.

19:52.460 --> 19:54.496
I think I'll play these.

19:59.880 --> 20:02.201
How old would your son be now?

20:04.670 --> 20:07.742
Seventeen?
Imagine what he could have become.

20:10.000 --> 20:12.207
Jacob put an end to any chance of that.

20:14.250 --> 20:17.538
Does the strain of your work
affect your marriage?

20:18.420 --> 20:20.957
-I'm not married.
-You wear a ring.

20:25.040 --> 20:27.782
Why would you still be protecting Jacob?

20:27.790 --> 20:31.453
Did you divorce because of putting
people like me away?

20:31.830 --> 20:33.878
I think you're innocent.

20:34.750 --> 20:36.661
We're all guilty of something.

20:38.330 --> 20:43.495
But it's our children that suffers
for our sins, isn't it?

20:46.380 --> 20:48.280
You'd have to ask him.

20:48.750 --> 20:50.286
How old is he?

20:52.920 --> 20:54.410
-He's 25.
-Oh!

20:56.330 --> 20:59.413
-Do you have a picture of him?
-In my office.

21:01.420 --> 21:03.991
-You don't carry him with you?
-No.

21:04.380 --> 21:05.995
To protect him.

21:07.750 --> 21:12.323
You want to leave him somewhere safe.
Somewhere clean.

21:14.460 --> 21:17.076
You killed Riley
to protect him from Jacob?

21:17.080 --> 21:19.822
I protect my son as you protect yours.

21:20.920 --> 21:22.490
Where's he buried?

21:22.500 --> 21:25.071
All that matters is that he's safe.

21:25.080 --> 21:27.287
-Where is he?
-He's in a better place.

21:31.420 --> 21:33.741
The chaplain's here to see you.

21:40.210 --> 21:43.202
What do you got?
-I got aces and eights. Two pair.

21:46.460 --> 21:48.280
The dead man's hand.

21:48.920 --> 21:52.708
I should have had that,
but then, of course, I would have lost.

21:52.710 --> 21:55.918
Straight to the jack.

21:57.080 --> 22:00.914
And unless the rules of poker
have changed since I've been in here,

22:00.920 --> 22:02.569
you lose.

22:04.790 --> 22:08.749
Oh, sorry. Full house. Aces over eights.

22:11.920 --> 22:13.069
Man,

22:14.750 --> 22:17.822
it would have been so nice.

22:21.080 --> 22:24.959
But to answer your question,
there are no other bodies.

22:31.420 --> 22:32.956
JJ.

22:36.210 --> 22:38.872
The Governor's just granted a stay
of execution to Sarah Jean.

22:38.880 --> 22:40.780
What? They can't do that.

22:40.790 --> 22:44.248
-They don't believe she killed your son.
-She killed him.

22:44.250 --> 22:46.491
I can tell you exactly where he's buried.

22:50.710 --> 22:53.702
It's got to be here.
Jacob built this gazebo.

22:53.710 --> 22:56.110
We've searched everywhere else.

22:59.500 --> 23:02.287
The workshop and extension
in Deb Mason's house had arches.

23:02.290 --> 23:05.418
I know he had to have built this one
for Riley.

23:08.380 --> 23:10.450
Hey, got something here.

23:26.790 --> 23:28.872
Guys, the body's ID's coming through.

23:28.880 --> 23:29.869
TUESDAY, 1PM
8 Hours Remaining

23:38.620 --> 23:40.167
It's not Riley Dawes.

23:40.170 --> 23:43.662
It's Ashley Farley.
She was 14 when she was killed.

23:43.670 --> 23:45.820
Why would Jacob give us another victim?

23:45.830 --> 23:49.414
It completely goes against his need
for power, manipulation and control.

23:49.420 --> 23:52.492
Taking the secret of an old victim
to his grave satisfies that need.

23:52.500 --> 23:54.240
Why give it up

23:54.250 --> 23:57.378
Sarah Jean's the payoff.
Sarah Jean will be his last victim.

23:57.380 --> 23:59.530
That'd be the ultimate of control.

23:59.540 --> 24:00.746
Gideon, check this out.

24:00.750 --> 24:03.036
Guess who used to be
the Farleys' house cleaner?

24:17.000 --> 24:20.322
My last supper. Like some?

24:20.750 --> 24:23.036
Look, came with a toy.

24:24.880 --> 24:26.950
-May I sit down?
-Please.

24:32.620 --> 24:34.576
Ashley Farley.

24:34.580 --> 24:37.492
You cleaned her parents' house. Remember?

24:38.120 --> 24:39.371
Fondly.

24:40.290 --> 24:43.578
We found her buried
beneath a children's gazebo.

24:44.080 --> 24:47.538
At another house Jacob renovated.
He put her there.

24:49.080 --> 24:52.243
I might as well have brought her home
to that bastard.

24:52.460 --> 24:53.916
Thanks, Doc.

24:56.000 --> 24:58.662
You lied to me. It wasn't Riley.

24:58.670 --> 25:01.412
-It wasn't?
-But she was 14 years old.

25:02.250 --> 25:04.241
Oh, and really pretty.

25:05.250 --> 25:07.377
How many others are there?

25:09.710 --> 25:13.168
I only have a few hours left and,
though I like you,

25:13.170 --> 25:16.162
and I do like you,

25:17.460 --> 25:19.530
I'd like to be alone now.

25:20.580 --> 25:22.616
Good meeting you, Hotch.

25:25.880 --> 25:28.451
-I'm not done yet.
-Oh, me neither.

25:39.960 --> 25:43.373
The high reeds. The river.

25:47.120 --> 25:50.283
This here, what is this, a basket?

25:52.670 --> 25:55.377
The boy in that painting is what, 10?

25:55.880 --> 25:57.324
Maybe more.

26:00.290 --> 26:03.202
Is that how you see him, or how he is?

26:04.670 --> 26:06.956
I only have a few hours left.

26:08.330 --> 26:10.662
I'm respectfully asking you to leave.

26:11.330 --> 26:14.709
Where is he

26:17.670 --> 26:19.456
Please see Agent Gideon out.

26:19.460 --> 26:20.825
Open four.

26:36.250 --> 26:38.616
Garcia, pull up the interview
with Sarah Jean.

26:38.620 --> 26:40.668
What is it?
-Exodus 2:3.

26:40.670 --> 26:42.035
Moses?

26:42.040 --> 26:44.326
Hebrew sons were supposed to be drowned.

26:44.710 --> 26:47.952
Moses' mother sent him down the Nile
in a basket.

26:47.960 --> 26:49.746
Where's he buried?

26:50.000 --> 26:51.786
All that matters is that he's safe.

26:52.460 --> 26:55.167
-Where is he?
-He's in a better place.

26:57.380 --> 26:59.826
Jacob didn't bury Riley anywhere.

27:00.420 --> 27:02.376
Sarah Jean had already taken care of him.

27:02.380 --> 27:03.745
Then she did kill him.

27:03.750 --> 27:07.072
No, she sent him somewhere
where she believed he'd be safe.

27:07.080 --> 27:08.616
He's alive.

27:11.620 --> 27:13.781
We're running out of time.

27:14.380 --> 27:16.701
This is the proof we need
to save Sarah Jean.

27:37.830 --> 27:41.163
Check all police and hospital records
dating back to September, 1990.

27:41.170 --> 27:43.240
You know, you should check
local newspapers, too.

27:43.250 --> 27:45.241
See if anyone reported
any abandoned babies.

27:45.250 --> 27:47.115
Yeah, I don't give a damn
where the Governor is.

27:47.120 --> 27:49.327
We may have found proof
that Sarah Jean is innocent.

27:49.330 --> 27:53.073
She really only had a maximum
of three hours between police visits.

27:53.670 --> 27:56.070
00 p.m.,
so traffic was pretty heaw.

27:56.080 --> 27:57.911
Whatever she did with Riley,
it had to be local.

27:57.920 --> 28:00.161
1990. Three babies were abandoned
in September.

28:00.170 --> 28:01.910
Two-year-old boys?

28:04.330 --> 28:05.661
None.

28:05.670 --> 28:07.661
Why doesn't she just tell us
where Riley is?

28:07.670 --> 28:09.615
She'll protect him
for as long as Jacob is alive.

28:09.620 --> 28:11.918
Look, they're being executed
within an hour of each other.

28:11.920 --> 28:13.740
What hope do we even have
of finding him in time?

28:13.750 --> 28:16.287
You know, it's quite possible she
doesn't even know where he is anyway.

28:16.290 --> 28:19.669
No. She'd know.
We've got to get into her cell.

28:27.670 --> 28:29.956
You come to see the show?

28:31.250 --> 28:33.320
We need to get into Sarah Jean's cell.

28:33.330 --> 28:35.457
-I believe the proof we...
-I can't do that.

28:35.460 --> 28:38.532
All official lines of communication
are now over.

28:38.540 --> 28:40.667
-I just need five minutes.
-Agent,

28:41.210 --> 28:44.702
they want the memory
of these two individuals erased.

28:49.620 --> 28:52.202
Five minutes. That's all I need.

28:53.380 --> 28:54.529
-Five minutes.
-Thank you.

28:54.540 --> 28:55.950
Come on.

29:01.830 --> 29:06.073
-I thought it was against regulations.
-Well, don't tell anybody.

29:09.580 --> 29:10.956
It's cold.

29:11.880 --> 29:14.531
You need a jacket.
Vincent, give me your jacket.

29:14.540 --> 29:19.660
Oh, no. I'm fine, really.
It makes me feel, you know, alive.

29:45.120 --> 29:48.374
-How are your sons, Warden?
-Well, they're good.

29:48.380 --> 29:49.745
Good.

29:49.750 --> 29:52.036
-Darren just graduated.
-Yeah?

29:53.420 --> 29:56.708
Did you ever tell them
about the man in the moon?

29:57.080 --> 29:58.286
Sure.

29:58.710 --> 30:00.530
I used to tell Riley

30:01.580 --> 30:03.912
that no matter where we were,

30:04.290 --> 30:07.327
the man in the moon
would be looking down on both of us.

30:47.210 --> 30:48.996
We should get back.

30:50.500 --> 30:55.278
Sarah, if there's something you know
that can save you...

30:55.290 --> 30:57.110
Thank you, Warden.

30:59.170 --> 31:01.536
This has been wonderful.

31:01.920 --> 31:05.037
Your kindness to me... I thank you.

31:09.880 --> 31:14.499
That's Riley. That's her son. Isn't it?
Someone tell me it's him, please.

31:16.540 --> 31:20.613
JJ, circulate this photo to the press.
See if anybody recognizes this boy.

31:20.620 --> 31:22.167
Do I say who we think he is?

31:22.170 --> 31:24.035
No, just put him out as a Missing Persons.

31:24.040 --> 31:25.280
Okay.

31:26.460 --> 31:28.030
What does that mean?

31:28.040 --> 31:31.669
It means Jacob is being moved
to the execution chamber.

31:35.330 --> 31:39.539
Sarah Jean! I'll be waiting for you.

31:40.290 --> 31:43.453
Do you wish to make your peace
with God, Jacob?

31:45.710 --> 31:50.830
I've made my peace 18 times,
and each one was prettier than him.

31:51.210 --> 31:53.531
Why take them with you, Jacob?

31:54.000 --> 31:55.490
You know why.

31:56.880 --> 31:58.416
Take him down.

31:58.710 --> 32:01.668
If you don't mind, gentlemen,

32:03.080 --> 32:05.913
this is one walk I can make myself.

32:17.580 --> 32:20.378
He's just confessed
to killing four more girls.

32:20.380 --> 32:22.450
There's nothing I can do.

32:47.000 --> 32:49.116
Are you ready, Sarah Jean?

32:49.710 --> 32:52.247
Going to ride the lightning, baby!

33:09.290 --> 33:12.874
She cut around the photo
so no one can read the text.

33:12.880 --> 33:15.030
He was two when he disappeared.

33:15.040 --> 33:16.746
This boy's 16 or 17.

33:16.750 --> 33:18.911
If it's Riley,
it would mean it's a recent photo.

33:18.920 --> 33:20.205
Once Jacob's dead,

33:20.210 --> 33:22.781
you think Sarah Jean will tell us
if this is Riley?

34:16.790 --> 34:18.371
Any last words?

34:20.460 --> 34:21.916
Bring it on.

34:31.000 --> 34:32.456
Riley.

34:35.580 --> 34:36.956
You lose.

34:37.250 --> 34:38.410
No!

35:16.500 --> 35:18.070
Jacob is gone.

35:20.080 --> 35:22.662
He's no longer any threat to Riley.

35:23.460 --> 35:27.669
Tell me where he is.
We can stop this madness.

35:28.380 --> 35:32.373
There is no greater gift in life
than that of being a parent.

35:35.250 --> 35:38.492
Yet so many of us abuse
and squander that gift.

35:39.580 --> 35:41.662
You can change that right now.

35:41.670 --> 35:44.070
I made my decision 15 years ago.

35:44.790 --> 35:47.247
This has never been about Jacob.

35:48.080 --> 35:49.911
It's always been about Riley.

35:50.420 --> 35:52.240
That's why I can't let you do this.

35:52.250 --> 35:55.413
-This isn't about you or me.
-I know it isn't.

35:56.540 --> 35:58.110
That's why I'm not going to let Riley lose

35:58.120 --> 35:59.826
the greatest gift he never knew he had.

35:59.830 --> 36:03.414
But that is my gift to him.
And I'll not let you destroy that.

36:06.380 --> 36:08.325
The only people Jacob allowed
Sarah Jean to know

36:08.330 --> 36:09.615
were the families she cleaned for.

36:09.620 --> 36:10.917
Sarah Jean worked for wealthy families,

36:10.920 --> 36:12.114
all of whom lived in Hampton.

36:12.120 --> 36:14.076
Let's go over all the families
in the state of Florida

36:14.080 --> 36:15.490
who were looking to adopt in 1990

36:15.500 --> 36:16.740
and let's see how many lived in Hampton.

36:16.750 --> 36:18.615
Families looking to adopt? Hundreds.

36:18.620 --> 36:20.576
-How many from Hampton?
-Three families.

36:20.580 --> 36:23.117
The Jameses, the Kopples
and the Sheffields.

36:23.120 --> 36:25.372
Looks like the Sheffields removed
themselves from the list

36:25.380 --> 36:27.701
in October 1990
and then moved out of Hampton.

36:27.710 --> 36:29.951
That's one month after Riley vanished.
Where'd they go?

36:29.960 --> 36:31.780
Keystone Heights.

36:31.790 --> 36:34.418
We got a match on the photo.
It was in the local daily news.

36:34.420 --> 36:37.412
Call Morgan and Elle.
Tell them to get to the Sheffield house.

36:37.420 --> 36:38.705
Byron Sheffield.

36:39.210 --> 36:42.373
"Local cello prodigy,
17-year-old Byron Sheffield,

36:42.380 --> 36:44.166
"won a scholarship to play cello."

36:48.670 --> 36:50.991
-How many miles to Keystone Heights?
-Way too many.

36:51.000 --> 36:52.319
We're never going to make it in time.

36:52.330 --> 36:53.877
Not if you keep running your mouth.

36:53.880 --> 36:56.201
Well, you better buckle up.

36:59.830 --> 37:02.879
We found him, Warden Diehl.
We found her son.

37:02.880 --> 37:06.202
Unless I _receive an official
stay of execution from the Governor,

37:06.210 --> 37:08.326
I am duty-bound to see this through.

37:08.330 --> 37:10.207
My son is dead, Agent Gideon.

37:10.210 --> 37:12.451
I have agents on the way
to his house as we speak,

37:12.460 --> 37:13.825
and the Governor is standing by.

37:13.830 --> 37:17.914
-Why can you not accept the truth?
-I can. This isn't it.

37:21.540 --> 37:24.327
My agents are within minutes of finding
her son alive.

37:26.120 --> 37:27.826
I am truly sorry.

37:29.460 --> 37:30.870
Hold here.

37:35.580 --> 37:38.162
What wouldn't you do for your son
to give him a life

37:38.170 --> 37:39.910
you could never hope to dream of?

37:42.290 --> 37:44.667
I am at peace in the knowledge

37:45.750 --> 37:49.242
that my son is free to be
whatever he chooses to be.

37:50.500 --> 37:52.570
If he knew who you were,

37:54.500 --> 37:57.242
do you think he'd choose to allow you
to walk in there?

37:58.710 --> 38:01.167
If he knew who his parents were,

38:02.880 --> 38:06.418
can you imagine the damage
my legacy would leave him?

38:07.620 --> 38:10.202
Can you imagine what he would feel

38:10.830 --> 38:14.038
knowing his mother spent 15 years
on death row,

38:14.380 --> 38:18.749
innocent of all charges,
just so he could be free of her?

38:18.750 --> 38:20.035
Not me.

38:20.750 --> 38:22.069
Jacob.

38:23.710 --> 38:28.875
It isn't just my life you have
in your hands, it's Riley's life, too.

38:31.170 --> 38:34.662
You have the chance to save my son's life.

38:35.960 --> 38:38.201
I choose to save yours, too.

38:39.710 --> 38:42.281
My life ended the day I met Jacob.

38:51.460 --> 38:53.496
Garcia. We made it.

38:54.670 --> 38:58.288
Hello

38:58.580 --> 39:00.992
Garcia, tell Gideon we're here.

39:01.420 --> 39:05.163
Yeah, but I'm afraid nobody else is.
Garcia, patch us through.

39:05.170 --> 39:06.319
Gideon, I've got Elle.

39:06.330 --> 39:08.707
She says they're at the Sheffield house.

39:08.710 --> 39:10.325
It's time.

39:10.330 --> 39:12.457
Take your hands off her.

39:12.460 --> 39:13.996
Tell Morgan to kick the door down
if he has to.

39:14.000 --> 39:16.207
Morgan, you're gonna get in the house,
whatever it takes.

39:16.210 --> 39:17.495
FBI!

39:17.500 --> 39:19.616
-I said take your hands off her.
-Agent Gideon.

39:19.620 --> 39:21.030
A few moments, please.

39:24.620 --> 39:25.917
FBI!

39:28.040 --> 39:29.371
Morgan.

39:40.290 --> 39:43.453
Just stay in the car. Can I help you?

39:43.460 --> 39:45.109
Frank Sheffield?

39:45.620 --> 39:48.168
-What is this about?
-This is about your son.

39:48.170 --> 39:49.569
My son.

39:52.830 --> 39:55.116
Is that your son in the car?

39:55.960 --> 39:59.248
I don't understand.
What is this about? Tell me.

39:59.620 --> 40:02.032
-We're federal agents.
-Hey, Hotch.

40:02.040 --> 40:04.167
We got him. He's here. What do we do?

40:04.170 --> 40:07.037
Gideon, they've got him.
What are we doing here, Gideon?

40:07.040 --> 40:10.168
I am standing here
because of choices I made.

40:13.420 --> 40:15.877
Don't let my son be Jacob's last victim.

40:18.960 --> 40:22.919
Let me go. Let us both go.

40:52.920 --> 40:54.319
Tell Morgan

40:56.210 --> 40:57.916
it's not her son.

40:59.040 --> 41:00.951
That we made a mistake.

41:01.920 --> 41:03.205
Let him go. It's not the boy.

41:06.790 --> 41:08.326
Hey, Derek.

41:11.960 --> 41:13.666
Wait there, sir.

41:28.460 --> 41:32.328
Mr. Sheffield, I'm very sorry.
We have the wrong house.

41:34.460 --> 41:36.917
I apologize for any inconvenience.

41:40.330 --> 41:41.536
Agent?

41:46.750 --> 41:48.115
Thank you.

42:11.290 --> 42:14.782
Would it be too much to ask
if yours is the last face I see?

43:53.540 --> 43:55.076
Albert Pine said,

43:55.080 --> 43:58.208
"What we do for ourselves dies with us.

43:58.210 --> 44:02.658
"What we do for others and the world
remains and is immortal."
